1
00:00:18,917 --> 00:00:22,017
[From landscape to portrait view]

2
00:00:22,017 --> 00:00:23,677
[Short dramas]

3
00:00:23,677 --> 00:00:25,067
[Short dramas are the trend now]

4
00:00:25,067 --> 00:00:26,677
[A new global trend]

5
00:00:26,677 --> 00:00:28,837
[Short-form dramas are trending]

6
00:00:28,837 --> 00:00:31,667
[Renowned directors are jumping
onto short dramas]

7
00:00:31,667 --> 00:00:33,437
[Even the masters joined the battlefield]

8
00:00:35,907 --> 00:00:36,910
[Short]

9
00:00:37,377 --> 00:00:38,430
[But more powerful]

10
00:00:39,527 --> 00:00:41,247
[Directors with impressive resumes]

11
00:00:41,247 --> 00:00:42,427
[It's all about the directing abilities]

12
00:00:43,157 --> 00:00:44,897
[New directors with unique qualities]

13
00:00:44,897 --> 00:00:47,367
[The competition starts
in the arena of their own]

14
00:00:51,937 --> 00:00:54,092
[The war of directors]

15
00:00:54,092 --> 00:00:57,272
[The war of short drama directors]

16
00:00:57,910 --> 00:01:01,097
[It starts now]

17
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:10,827
[Someone is on the Director's Arena stage]

18
00:01:10,827 --> 00:01:12,241
What? What's this?

19
00:01:12,241 --> 00:01:15,412
[Who's the first contestant?]

20
00:01:18,530 --> 00:01:20,754
[He looks somewhat familiar]

21
00:01:20,754 --> 00:01:22,264
I'm so nervous.

22
00:01:23,144 --> 00:01:25,974
Hello, I'm actor Lee Joo Seung.

23
00:01:25,974 --> 00:01:28,864
I've directed a play, a feature film,

24
00:01:28,864 --> 00:01:31,864
a TV drama, and a short film.

25
00:01:31,864 --> 00:01:34,004
But I've never directed a short-form drama.

26
00:01:34,004 --> 00:01:35,914
So, I decided to apply.

27
00:01:36,524 --> 00:01:39,074
[Blown away]

28
00:01:39,547 --> 00:01:43,154
I could sense this was something new.

29
00:01:43,154 --> 00:01:45,597
The show will be on TV,

30
00:01:45,597 --> 00:01:48,597
but there were three vertical
screens on the stage.

31
00:01:48,597 --> 00:01:51,687
I thought this was a revolution
and a new attempt.

32
00:01:51,687 --> 00:01:53,637
It got me excited.

33
00:01:53,637 --> 00:01:56,417
Wow, this place is huge.

34
00:01:56,417 --> 00:01:59,277
There are so many of them.

35
00:01:59,277 --> 00:02:01,287
I'm nervous.

36
00:02:01,287 --> 00:02:03,197
[The seasoned actor is nervous]

37
00:02:04,857 --> 00:02:07,297
[Two directors are entering, smiling brightly]

38
00:02:07,297 --> 00:02:09,707
The production quality is amazing.

39
00:02:09,707 --> 00:02:12,577
Wow, how much did this set cost?

40
00:02:12,577 --> 00:02:17,397
You could make three
short dramas with this budget.

41
00:02:17,397 --> 00:02:20,307
I'm a YouTuber with almost a million subscribers.

42
00:02:20,307 --> 00:02:25,327
I feel like this is an extension
of my YouTube content.

43
00:02:25,327 --> 00:02:27,577
I've been playing alone in my own league.

44
00:02:27,577 --> 00:02:32,167
I felt nervous but excited for once.

45
00:02:32,167 --> 00:02:35,297
- Hello.
- Hello.

46
00:02:35,297 --> 00:02:36,917
You're a celebrity.

47
00:02:36,917 --> 00:02:38,767
I'm a fan.

48
00:02:40,277 --> 00:02:43,247
Wow, they must've spent so much.

49
00:02:44,557 --> 00:02:46,267
Is this what the TV industry is like?

50
00:02:46,267 --> 00:02:48,347
I couldn't help but go, "Wow."

51
00:02:48,347 --> 00:02:50,677
They spent more than I thought.

52
00:02:50,677 --> 00:02:55,107
Wow, it's an arena for directors.

53
00:02:55,107 --> 00:02:58,647
I'm expecting to see many impressive people.

54
00:02:58,647 --> 00:03:02,147
I'm here because I want to compete.

55
00:03:02,147 --> 00:03:06,297
There's a short drama I really enjoyed.

56
00:03:06,297 --> 00:03:10,237
The director of that drama was there.

57
00:03:10,237 --> 00:03:12,287
Director Jang Ji Won.

58
00:03:13,937 --> 00:03:17,207
I directed 20 short-form dramas.

59
00:03:17,207 --> 00:03:18,957
I want to become the Bong Joon Ho of short-form.

60
00:03:18,957 --> 00:03:21,487
I'm the Bong Joon Ho of the BL genre now.

61
00:03:21,487 --> 00:03:23,187
Look.

62
00:03:23,187 --> 00:03:25,387
[Can sense a presence of a master]

63
00:03:25,387 --> 00:03:27,157
Why say you did a bad job?

64
00:03:27,157 --> 00:03:32,127
Hello, I'm director Han Soo Ji,
and I've directed many youth dramas,

65
00:03:32,127 --> 00:03:34,357
including "Eighteen."

66
00:03:34,357 --> 00:03:36,187
She's really talented.

67
00:03:36,187 --> 00:03:41,647
The project I was working on
got canceled last year.

68
00:03:41,647 --> 00:03:43,757
I haven't been doing much.

69
00:03:43,757 --> 00:03:47,887
So, I was hoping to get a lot of work.

70
00:03:49,287 --> 00:03:55,637
I thought this was a competition
among inexperienced directors.

71
00:03:55,637 --> 00:03:58,127
But many of them are very seasoned.

72
00:03:58,127 --> 00:04:02,657
If I could go back in time,
I wouldn't have applied.

73
00:04:02,657 --> 00:04:05,547
[Another contestant is entering alone]

74
00:04:05,547 --> 00:04:08,607
[Actor Lee Yoo Jin]

75
00:04:08,607 --> 00:04:11,387
[My gosh]

76
00:04:11,387 --> 00:04:14,097
[Where are the cameras?]

77
00:04:14,637 --> 00:04:17,267
[Sudden appearance of handsomeness]

78
00:04:17,267 --> 00:04:20,997
If someone handsome like him makes a V,

79
00:04:20,997 --> 00:04:23,647
my V will get edited out.

80
00:04:23,647 --> 00:04:27,487
- I know.
- He's too handsome to do that.

81
00:04:27,487 --> 00:04:28,947
Over here.

82
00:04:30,367 --> 00:04:32,187
And he's sitting in front of us.

83
00:04:32,987 --> 00:04:34,827
Nice to meet you.

84
00:04:34,827 --> 00:04:36,757
When I saw the name,

85
00:04:36,757 --> 00:04:40,047
I thought it might be you. I was right.

86
00:04:40,047 --> 00:04:44,497
- The actors are sitting in front of us.
- I know. Why here?

87
00:04:44,497 --> 00:04:46,717
[Very uncomfortable]

88
00:04:46,717 --> 00:04:49,537
[More actors are coming]

89
00:04:49,537 --> 00:04:51,397
[Actress Ahn Mi Na]

90
00:04:51,397 --> 00:04:54,197
This will be tough.

91
00:04:54,197 --> 00:05:02,487
I was reminded of how much
actors are interested in directing.

92
00:05:02,487 --> 00:05:09,047
But I wanted to become a director
even before I became an actor.

93
00:05:09,047 --> 00:05:11,147
So, I thought I was better.

94
00:05:11,727 --> 00:05:12,827
[Hehe]

95
00:05:13,347 --> 00:05:17,047
- Wow.
- He's wearing hanbok.

96
00:05:17,047 --> 00:05:20,847
[High school-aged directors in school uniforms]

97
00:05:20,847 --> 00:05:22,427
They're kids.

98
00:05:22,427 --> 00:05:24,047
[It's my thumbnail]

99
00:05:24,047 --> 00:05:27,217
There's "Judo Situation."

100
00:05:27,217 --> 00:05:30,547
Did they get these thumbnails made?

101
00:05:30,547 --> 00:05:33,967
- Is that Choi Gwi Hwa?
- It's him.

102
00:05:33,967 --> 00:05:36,027
Choi Gwi Hwa is here, too.

103
00:05:36,027 --> 00:05:39,197
- Gwi Hwa. Wow.
- We're in trouble.

104
00:05:39,197 --> 00:05:41,107
He should join the judges instead.

105
00:05:41,107 --> 00:05:42,827
[Charismatic like a judge]

106
00:05:42,827 --> 00:05:45,017
Is he here to shoot something else?

107
00:05:45,017 --> 00:05:47,927
[All 33 directors have entered]

108
00:05:47,927 --> 00:05:50,257
[Everyone is getting up]

109
00:05:50,257 --> 00:05:51,647
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

110
00:05:51,647 --> 00:05:54,277
[It's like a fan meeting]

111
00:05:55,237 --> 00:05:57,487
If I get eliminated in the first round,

112
00:05:57,487 --> 00:06:01,427
please hire me as an actor.

113
00:06:01,427 --> 00:06:04,997
- I'd be happy to work with you.
- Yes, absolutely.

114
00:06:06,417 --> 00:06:11,367
Since COVID, not just the production crew,

115
00:06:11,367 --> 00:06:14,757
but actors also have fewer projects to work on.

116
00:06:14,757 --> 00:06:19,077
I'm hoping to fulfill my desire to create.

117
00:06:19,077 --> 00:06:20,977
I just wanted to work on my project.

118
00:06:20,977 --> 00:06:23,587
I've been wanting to work on projects,

119
00:06:23,587 --> 00:06:25,427
but it's hard to find investors.

120
00:06:25,427 --> 00:06:27,217
But I came across this opportunity.

121
00:06:27,217 --> 00:06:30,687
I thought I could make some money with this.

122
00:06:30,687 --> 00:06:32,957
[To discover new directors]

123
00:06:32,957 --> 00:06:35,007
[The Top 7 will be funded
to produce short-form dramas]

124
00:06:35,007 --> 00:06:37,087
[The winner will win 100 million won]

125
00:06:37,087 --> 00:06:40,117
[The fierce competition of directors starts now]

126
00:06:40,117 --> 00:06:42,497
[The cheering is signaling the start]

127
00:06:43,667 --> 00:06:46,757
Hello, hello.

128
00:06:46,757 --> 00:06:50,137
Hello, nice to meet you.

129
00:06:50,137 --> 00:06:53,997
Korea's first-ever short drama
directing survival competition.

130
00:06:53,997 --> 00:06:56,987
Welcome to Director's Arena, everyone.

131
00:06:56,987 --> 00:06:59,067
[Director's Arena]

132
00:06:59,067 --> 00:07:02,517
With the dopamine-stimulating
fresh material and quick pace,

133
00:07:02,517 --> 00:07:06,057
short dramas draw you in more than TV dramas.

134
00:07:06,057 --> 00:07:10,657
They've become killer content
that leads the content industry.

135
00:07:10,657 --> 00:07:17,227
You'll fall in love with the short
but impactful world of shorts.

136
00:07:17,227 --> 00:07:24,067
To create the nation's short drama,
33 directors joined the Director's Arena.

137
00:07:24,067 --> 00:07:26,297
Before I introduce the directors,

138
00:07:26,297 --> 00:07:32,687
let me introduce you to the Five Stars,
who will be judging the short dramas.

139
00:07:32,687 --> 00:07:37,997
He's a top-tier actor who's been
proving his versatility for 33 years.

140
00:07:37,997 --> 00:07:40,157
Our forever prince of the Korean wave.

141
00:07:40,157 --> 00:07:42,807
Please welcome Jang Keun Suk.

142
00:07:42,807 --> 00:07:44,267
[Daebak]

143
00:07:45,667 --> 00:07:47,047
Gosh.

144
00:07:47,047 --> 00:07:50,427
[Actor Jang Keun Suk]

145
00:07:50,427 --> 00:07:54,317
This actor is a true all-rounder.

146
00:07:54,317 --> 00:07:56,657
Please welcome Cha Tae Hyun.

147
00:07:56,657 --> 00:07:59,047
[Cheer for him]

148
00:07:59,612 --> 00:08:02,707
[Actor Cha Tae Hyun]

149
00:08:02,707 --> 00:08:07,037
He's the nation's director who
recently created a hit short drama.

150
00:08:07,037 --> 00:08:08,827
He's known for his witty dialogues.

151
00:08:08,827 --> 00:08:11,787
Please welcome Lee Byeong Heon.

152
00:08:11,787 --> 00:08:13,147
[Wow]

153
00:08:14,687 --> 00:08:18,082
[Director Lee Byeong Heon]

154
00:08:18,082 --> 00:08:19,527
[The judges have a strong presence]

155
00:08:19,527 --> 00:08:22,767
They definitely had strong auras.

156
00:08:22,767 --> 00:08:25,507
I felt intimidated.

157
00:08:25,507 --> 00:08:27,717
They're such impressive people.

158
00:08:27,717 --> 00:08:32,877
All of them have impressive resumes.

159
00:08:32,877 --> 00:08:37,157
They've reached peak success
in their respective fields.

160
00:08:37,157 --> 00:08:40,277
How do the top-tier talents see things?

161
00:08:40,277 --> 00:08:42,257
I was curious about that.

162
00:08:42,257 --> 00:08:44,217
We're joined by the three judges.

163
00:08:44,217 --> 00:08:47,037
Keun Suk, do you watch a lot of short dramas?

164
00:08:47,037 --> 00:08:50,587
I do all the time. I'm basically addicted.

165
00:08:50,587 --> 00:08:52,617
There are so many fun ones.

166
00:08:52,617 --> 00:08:57,817
I was curious if I could come up
with a great story, too.

167
00:08:57,817 --> 00:09:00,757
So, I've made one with a friend of mine.

168
00:09:00,757 --> 00:09:03,667
What do you think is unique about short dramas?

169
00:09:03,667 --> 00:09:05,097
It's not easy.

170
00:09:05,097 --> 00:09:08,807
You have to capture everything
in such a short time.

171
00:09:08,807 --> 00:09:11,197
I remember working on that a lot.

172
00:09:11,197 --> 00:09:12,757
Thank you.

173
00:09:12,757 --> 00:09:16,637
Tae Hyun, you're a known fan of audition shows.

174
00:09:16,637 --> 00:09:21,947
Yes. I'm thankfully in a lot
of audition shows lately.

175
00:09:21,947 --> 00:09:24,477
But I didn't think I'd be in one like this.

176
00:09:24,477 --> 00:09:26,557
Short drama audition?

177
00:09:26,557 --> 00:09:29,697
How do you judge a short drama audition?

178
00:09:29,697 --> 00:09:31,577
Short drama audition?

179
00:09:31,577 --> 00:09:33,317
What kind of accent is that?

180
00:09:33,317 --> 00:09:35,797
You say "short" funny like this.

181
00:09:35,797 --> 00:09:39,457
I don't know much about them
since I don't watch them.

182
00:09:39,457 --> 00:09:42,707
But I hear they're becoming more popular.

183
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:44,467
Yes, that's the trend.

184
00:09:44,467 --> 00:09:47,737
It's about time I start becoming interested.

185
00:09:47,737 --> 00:09:50,241
People don't hire me that much anymore.

186
00:09:50,241 --> 00:09:53,147
- Really?
- I'm here for a personal reason.

187
00:09:53,147 --> 00:09:54,747
Hoping to appear in one?

188
00:09:54,747 --> 00:09:57,137
That's basically 50% of my goal.

189
00:09:57,137 --> 00:09:59,227
Really? Everyone...

190
00:09:59,227 --> 00:10:03,347
I want to network here

191
00:10:03,347 --> 00:10:06,747
and appear in a short drama.

192
00:10:06,747 --> 00:10:10,597
- Really?
- I have a selfish motive, too.

193
00:10:10,597 --> 00:10:16,087
I need to find talented directors as a producer.

194
00:10:16,087 --> 00:10:17,717
That's my personal reason.

195
00:10:17,717 --> 00:10:24,577
The short drama you created
is the No. 1 right now.

196
00:10:24,577 --> 00:10:31,457
You might be the biggest role model
for the directors here.

197
00:10:31,457 --> 00:10:33,627
Everyone here has a strong personality.

198
00:10:33,627 --> 00:10:36,107
I don't think that's true.

199
00:10:36,107 --> 00:10:38,567
You're a straight shooter.

200
00:10:38,567 --> 00:10:44,187
You introduced us as Five Stars earlier.

201
00:10:44,187 --> 00:10:47,427
Who are the other two, then?

202
00:10:47,427 --> 00:10:51,517
The other two?
We have an empty chair in the studio.

203
00:10:51,517 --> 00:10:53,567
Someone will have to sit there.

204
00:10:53,567 --> 00:10:55,967
That's me!

205
00:10:55,967 --> 00:10:57,377
Welcome. Join us.

206
00:10:57,377 --> 00:11:00,117
- May I?
- You're joining us right away.

207
00:11:00,117 --> 00:11:02,217
One seat is for Do Yeon.

208
00:11:02,217 --> 00:11:04,767
- Who takes the last seat?
- The last seat is for...

209
00:11:04,767 --> 00:11:08,997
the 34 viewers who are more
ruthless than anyone.

210
00:11:08,997 --> 00:11:10,347
Welcome.

211
00:11:10,347 --> 00:11:16,227
[The 34 viewers will be judging as well]

212
00:11:16,227 --> 00:11:19,867
The first thing I noticed is these.
Thumbnails, right?

213
00:11:19,867 --> 00:11:21,767
- Right.
- Thumbnails.

214
00:11:21,767 --> 00:11:25,247
I'm curious how important they are.

215
00:11:25,247 --> 00:11:28,277
It literally means a fingernail.

216
00:11:28,277 --> 00:11:31,487
It's an image as big as a thumbnail.

217
00:11:31,487 --> 00:11:35,207
The image is important, but so is the text.

218
00:11:35,207 --> 00:11:37,287
The titles are very direct, too.

219
00:11:37,287 --> 00:11:39,747
They're saying, "Look at me. What do you think?"

220
00:11:39,747 --> 00:11:41,167
They make you look.

221
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:42,807
What are you drawn to?

222
00:11:42,807 --> 00:11:45,757
I think it has to do with your personality.

223
00:11:45,757 --> 00:11:47,677
The "Five Generation Family" sticks out the most.

224
00:11:47,677 --> 00:11:50,087
It sticks out to me because it's so positive.

225
00:11:50,087 --> 00:11:52,637
It has to be different as well.

226
00:11:52,637 --> 00:11:55,737
You're right. The girl's smile is so innocent.

227
00:11:55,737 --> 00:11:59,597
"Is this Marriage Valid?" seems to say,
"What's with you?"

228
00:11:59,597 --> 00:12:02,057
- "Is this Marriage Valid?"
- Over here.

229
00:12:02,057 --> 00:12:05,167
I noticed it when I came in, too.

230
00:12:05,167 --> 00:12:07,447
I yelled, "Yes!" inside.

231
00:12:07,447 --> 00:12:10,215
My intention was to be noticed.

232
00:12:10,215 --> 00:12:12,716
What about you, Tae Hyun?

233
00:12:12,716 --> 00:12:17,555
I noticed the "Judo Situation."

234
00:12:17,555 --> 00:12:19,540
["Judo Situation" caught his eye]

235
00:12:19,540 --> 00:12:20,491
[Laugh]

236
00:12:20,491 --> 00:12:22,767
"Judo Situation*."
(It could also mean "ejaculation")

237
00:12:22,767 --> 00:12:24,917
- "Judo Situation."
- "Judo Situation."

238
00:12:24,917 --> 00:12:26,937
The one called "Judo Situation."

239
00:12:26,937 --> 00:12:29,997
- Doesn't it sound erotic?
- What's the situation?

240
00:12:29,997 --> 00:12:33,387
- What situation is it?
- Many different situations.

241
00:12:33,387 --> 00:12:35,627
I think mine was the best.

242
00:12:36,667 --> 00:12:38,187
Let's try that again.

243
00:12:38,187 --> 00:12:39,647
[Will be revealed soon]

244
00:12:39,647 --> 00:12:44,927
What stories are hiding behind the thumbnails?

245
00:12:44,927 --> 00:12:47,807
Let me reveal the Round 1 mission.

246
00:12:47,807 --> 00:12:50,197
[Round 1 mission is being revealed]

247
00:12:50,197 --> 00:12:53,087
[Round 1 mission]

248
00:12:53,087 --> 00:12:55,977
[Create a 90-second teaser]

249
00:12:55,977 --> 00:12:57,757
[Not easy...]

250
00:12:57,757 --> 00:13:02,307
The time limit will bring a lot of pressure.

251
00:13:02,307 --> 00:13:04,837
They must want to say a lot,

252
00:13:04,837 --> 00:13:10,107
but you have to compress it into a trailer.

253
00:13:10,107 --> 00:13:12,257
- That's right.
- Think of it as that.

254
00:13:12,257 --> 00:13:15,497
They were told about the
mission in advance, right?

255
00:13:15,497 --> 00:13:20,187
That's right. We revealed the
mission two weeks ago.

256
00:13:20,187 --> 00:13:26,287
The directors created 90-second
teasers for their short dramas.

257
00:13:26,287 --> 00:13:28,187
[2 weeks ago]

258
00:13:28,187 --> 00:13:31,187
[Each team was given the Round 1 mission]

259
00:13:31,187 --> 00:13:32,337
Ready.

260
00:13:32,337 --> 00:13:33,307
[Show everything in 90 seconds]

261
00:13:33,307 --> 00:13:34,257
Action.

262
