[Judo Situation]

1030
00:53:37,197 --> 00:53:38,787
[What kind of...]

1031
00:53:39,747 --> 00:53:44,107
[story do you want?]

1032
00:53:45,487 --> 00:53:46,797
[Like this?]

1033
00:53:46,797 --> 00:53:52,837
[Bombs exploding, cars racing, and fight scenes?]

1034
00:53:57,437 --> 00:54:01,027
[The air is going cold]

1035
00:54:01,027 --> 00:54:05,057
We kept seeing the movies we've seen.

1036
00:54:05,057 --> 00:54:09,397
It was disappointing because
I wanted to see his work.

1037
00:54:09,397 --> 00:54:12,027
The text was too long in the beginning.

1038
00:54:12,027 --> 00:54:14,447
[The air is getting heavy]

1039
00:54:15,057 --> 00:54:17,687
[Voting starts]

1040
00:54:17,687 --> 00:54:20,047
[Viewers are pressing stop without hesitation]

1041
00:54:21,047 --> 00:54:23,167
[Stop count explodes]

1042
00:54:23,167 --> 00:54:26,357
[Turns out it's an unfortunate situation]

1043
00:54:26,357 --> 00:54:30,287
I knew I messed up. Something went wrong.

1044
00:54:30,287 --> 00:54:31,957
I misjudged.

1045
00:54:31,957 --> 00:54:35,097
[The stop count is skyrocketing]

1046
00:54:35,097 --> 00:54:38,377
[Oh, no...]

1047
00:54:38,377 --> 00:54:39,617
[A crazy girl]

1048
00:54:40,047 --> 00:54:41,857
[One vote away from stopping video]

1049
00:54:41,857 --> 00:54:45,327
[Will he be eliminated like this?]

1050
00:54:45,327 --> 00:54:52,477
[What will happen to "Judo Situation"?]

1051
00:54:56,097 --> 00:54:58,947
[Director Seo Seong Won is eliminated!]

1052
00:54:58,947 --> 00:55:01,467
[Gosh...]

1053
00:55:01,467 --> 00:55:04,117
[Stunned]

1054
00:55:04,117 --> 00:55:06,137
[The video was cut off for the first time]

1055
00:55:06,137 --> 00:55:08,727
- Unfortunately...
- What was that?

1056
00:55:08,727 --> 00:55:10,737
The video was stopped.

1057
00:55:10,737 --> 00:55:14,837
I thought it was risky while watching it.

1058
00:55:14,837 --> 00:55:19,387
I've been waiting for the main part to start.

1059
00:55:19,387 --> 00:55:21,497
It was about to, but it stopped.

1060
00:55:21,497 --> 00:55:23,627
It gets interesting later.

1061
00:55:23,627 --> 00:55:25,567
[Hehe]

1062
00:55:25,567 --> 00:55:27,027
I was shocked.

1063
00:55:27,027 --> 00:55:30,117
It was about to start with
a full shot, but it stopped.

1064
00:55:30,117 --> 00:55:32,057
I was shocked.

1065
00:55:32,057 --> 00:55:34,787
What did you think, Tae Hyun? He's passed out.

1066
00:55:34,787 --> 00:55:37,207
It was your one pick.

1067
00:55:37,207 --> 00:55:40,417
- You can't watch it anymore.
- What happened, Director?

1068
00:55:40,417 --> 00:55:45,917
- Come on and tell us.
- When the text appeared on the screen,

1069
00:55:45,917 --> 00:55:48,137
- I thought, "He's in trouble."
- Really?

1070
00:55:48,137 --> 00:55:50,767
I think he misjudged.

1071
00:55:50,767 --> 00:55:54,027
I want to hear from you, too.

1072
00:55:54,027 --> 00:55:56,997
We watched many teasers before this.

1073
00:55:56,997 --> 00:56:01,517
While watching them, I thought, "I'm screwed."

1074
00:56:02,557 --> 00:56:04,407
He's so honest.

1075
00:56:04,407 --> 00:56:06,847
Especially the one who went right before me.

1076
00:56:06,847 --> 00:56:09,237
[The guilty one]

1077
00:56:09,237 --> 00:56:11,237
That teaser was amazing.

1078
00:56:11,237 --> 00:56:13,057
- "I'm screwed."
- "Ladder" was too powerful.

1079
00:56:13,057 --> 00:56:14,227
I had to go right after that.

1080
00:56:14,227 --> 00:56:16,737
- You raised the bar too high.
- Apologize. Apologize.

1081
00:56:16,737 --> 00:56:18,377
I had to go right after that.

1082
00:56:18,377 --> 00:56:22,747
Wasn't this the most controversial one so far?

1083
00:56:22,747 --> 00:56:27,157
You never know. Getting people
to talk is most crucial.

1084
00:56:27,157 --> 00:56:30,157
Right. He's No. 1 in that regard.

1085
00:56:30,157 --> 00:56:31,847
Director Seo, thank you.

1086
00:56:31,847 --> 00:56:35,847
It is a shame, but please return to
your seat and continue voting.

1087
00:56:36,847 --> 00:56:38,707
You can't go home. I'm sorry.

1088
00:56:38,707 --> 00:56:41,167
I want to go... Thank you.

1089
00:56:41,167 --> 00:56:43,897
[The most controversial director, Seo Seong Won]

1090
00:56:43,897 --> 00:56:47,847
I was shocked that everyone shot the teaser.

1091
00:56:47,847 --> 00:56:51,247
I can't complain about being at the bottom.

1092
00:56:51,247 --> 00:56:54,187
I'm a bit embarrassed.

1093
00:56:55,317 --> 00:56:59,177
I want to watch "Kill Order" next.

1094
00:56:59,177 --> 00:57:00,687
Please come forward.

1095
00:57:00,687 --> 00:57:02,307
- Fighting.
- Fighting.

1096
00:57:02,307 --> 00:57:03,387
[Everyone is cheering]

1097
00:57:03,387 --> 00:57:07,047
Director Jang Ji Won.

1098
00:57:07,047 --> 00:57:08,847
[Heart pounding]

1099
00:57:08,847 --> 00:57:12,017
[The thumbnail hints at an intense action]

1100
00:57:12,017 --> 00:57:13,857
It must be scary.

1101
00:57:13,857 --> 00:57:15,867
It looks action-packed.

1102
00:57:15,867 --> 00:57:18,107
This is nerve-racking.

1103
00:57:18,107 --> 00:57:21,477
You shouldn't be nervous.
Didn't you see Director Seo?

1104
00:57:21,477 --> 00:57:23,327
None of you should be nervous.

1105
00:57:23,327 --> 00:57:25,667
Consider yourself lucky to go after him.

1106
00:57:25,667 --> 00:57:29,177
That's right. It takes good luck to go after him.

1107
00:57:29,177 --> 00:57:33,507
- I can't do this.
- Don't be nervous. Go ahead.

1108
00:57:33,507 --> 00:57:39,227
Hello, I've been dreaming about
directing since I was in school.

1109
00:57:39,227 --> 00:57:42,127
I've been making films since I was in the US.

1110
00:57:42,127 --> 00:57:44,757
I'm Jang Ji Won, a short drama director.

1111
00:57:44,757 --> 00:57:48,927
I had a project in 2024.

1112
00:57:48,927 --> 00:57:53,187
"Die or Punch" is about to be released soon.

1113
00:57:53,187 --> 00:57:59,387
I think action genre is my forte.

1114
00:57:59,387 --> 00:58:02,177
Since the vertical screen is narrow,

1115
00:58:02,177 --> 00:58:04,137
it's challenging for action.

1116
00:58:04,137 --> 00:58:07,637
Every move needs to be visible.

1117
00:58:07,637 --> 00:58:11,767
That way, you know how the action progresses.

1118
00:58:11,767 --> 00:58:15,747
That's what I focused on when we filmed.

1119
00:58:16,677 --> 00:58:20,757
Let's watch Director Jang Ji Won's teaser.

1120
00:58:20,757 --> 00:58:22,377
Play the video.

1121
00:58:22,377 --> 00:58:26,727
A retired hitman is working as a deliveryman.

1122
00:58:26,727 --> 00:58:29,827
But the people he delivered
packages to started dying.

1123
00:58:29,827 --> 00:58:33,107
He tracks down the killer
in this action thriller.

1124
00:58:36,647 --> 00:58:39,867
[The teaser is speaking with action]

1125
00:58:39,867 --> 00:58:44,947
[Jang Ji Won's "Kill Order"]

1126
00:59:14,027 --> 00:59:16,777
[The stop count is going up unexpectedly]

1127
00:59:16,777 --> 00:59:20,187
[Eyes shaking]

1128
00:59:20,187 --> 00:59:23,517
People don't like action.

1129
00:59:23,517 --> 00:59:26,857
The boxes you sent... I delivered them.

1130
00:59:26,857 --> 00:59:29,567
- You know, right?
- I don't.

1131
00:59:33,497 --> 00:59:36,667
Who sent the package?

1132
00:59:37,627 --> 00:59:39,477
F*** off.

1133
00:59:39,477 --> 00:59:42,497
You're nothing but a delivery guy.

1134
00:59:47,737 --> 00:59:51,347
[The stop count is going up as the action starts]

1135
00:59:55,327 --> 00:59:57,827
[So close to the video stopping]

1136
00:59:57,827 --> 01:00:00,937
I was freaking nervous. Seriously.

1137
01:00:00,937 --> 01:00:02,827
I just didn't want it to stop.

1138
01:00:02,827 --> 01:00:05,567
I wanted people to see the whole thing.

1139
01:00:05,567 --> 01:00:07,987
["Kill Order" is about to be killed]

1140
01:00:07,987 --> 01:00:12,247
[Will it play all the way to the end?]

1141
01:00:16,447 --> 01:00:19,347
[Kill Order]

1142
01:00:21,897 --> 01:00:24,667
[He survived by one vote]

1143
01:00:27,417 --> 01:00:29,407
What's the deal?

1144
01:00:29,407 --> 01:00:32,557
[Has a chance to survive,
but feels like he's eliminated...]

1145
01:00:32,557 --> 01:00:34,667
That was a close one.

1146
01:00:34,667 --> 01:00:36,667
That's spiking my dopamine.

1147
01:00:36,667 --> 01:00:38,227
[This is a short drama!]

1148
01:00:38,227 --> 01:00:39,777
That was so close.

1149
01:00:39,777 --> 01:00:41,377
It was a close call.

1150
01:00:41,377 --> 01:00:44,237
You almost joined Director Seo Seong Won.

1151
01:00:44,237 --> 01:00:46,677
It was one vote away.

1152
01:00:46,677 --> 01:00:48,437
I made it.

1153
01:00:48,437 --> 01:00:53,127
Wow. I was torn, but I decided not to push it.

1154
01:00:53,127 --> 01:00:54,777
It could've been bad.

1155
01:00:54,777 --> 01:00:58,817
I get that it's an action film.

1156
01:00:58,817 --> 01:01:00,987
But that was all I saw.

1157
01:01:00,987 --> 01:01:05,317
I think I've already gotten used to short dramas.

1158
01:01:05,317 --> 01:01:07,247
So, it has to move along.

1159
01:01:07,247 --> 01:01:09,777
I thought I should be seeing more.

1160
01:01:09,777 --> 01:01:12,387
The dopamine keeps...

1161
01:01:12,387 --> 01:01:15,157
- I'm in trouble.
- We got used to dopamine.

1162
01:01:15,157 --> 01:01:18,117
Watching this teaser,

1163
01:01:18,117 --> 01:01:20,427
I got hooked very quickly.

1164
01:01:20,427 --> 01:01:22,917
But I got unhooked quickly, too.

1165
01:01:22,917 --> 01:01:27,497
I was wondering when I felt that.

1166
01:01:27,497 --> 01:01:34,617
It wasn't clear what the
dialogue was leading us to.

1167
01:01:34,617 --> 01:01:39,957
I think I fell out of it after that.

1168
01:01:39,957 --> 01:01:44,977
Jang Keun Suk said he got
hooked and unhooked quickly.

1169
01:01:44,977 --> 01:01:50,287
That's when I realized I didn't strategize well.

1170
01:01:50,287 --> 01:01:52,647
- Yes.
- Thank you.

1171
01:01:52,647 --> 01:01:54,647
Gosh.

1172
01:01:54,647 --> 01:01:57,147
This is pretty intense.

1173
01:01:57,147 --> 01:02:02,407
I can tell you've seen a lot
of short dramas, Keun Suk.

1174
01:02:02,407 --> 01:02:04,347
- He's sharp.
- He is.

1175
01:02:04,347 --> 01:02:08,047
- I'm just pretending.
- He's on another level.

1176
01:02:08,047 --> 01:02:12,937
- He's educating me a lot.
- We're learning a lot.

1177
01:02:12,937 --> 01:02:15,537
Let's welcome the next director.

1178
01:02:15,537 --> 01:02:18,587
The next director is...

1179
01:02:18,587 --> 01:02:23,407
"Cast Them If You See the Path."
Please come forward.

1180
01:02:23,407 --> 01:02:26,867
[His looks are lifting the vibe immediately]

1181
01:02:27,657 --> 01:02:30,667
"Cast Them If You See the Path."

1182
01:02:30,667 --> 01:02:32,567
So handsome.

1183
01:02:32,567 --> 01:02:34,607
[Who's this person?]

1184
01:02:34,607 --> 01:02:37,477
- Huh? He looks familiar.
- Very familiar.

1185
01:02:37,477 --> 01:02:39,777
Director Lee Yoo Jin.

1186
01:02:39,777 --> 01:02:41,177
[We've seen him as an actor]

1187
01:02:41,177 --> 01:02:43,327
Please introduce yourself.

1188
01:02:43,327 --> 01:02:47,527
Hello, I've been acting for 12 years

1189
01:02:47,527 --> 01:02:52,777
and now I'm an actor... Let me try that again.

1190
01:02:52,777 --> 01:02:54,647
Fighting!

1191
01:02:54,647 --> 01:02:56,847
So handsome!

1192
01:02:56,847 --> 01:03:00,567
Everyone must be nervous.
I didn't think he'd be nervous at all.

1193
01:03:00,567 --> 01:03:03,237
You're the last person who should be nervous.

1194
01:03:03,237 --> 01:03:05,487
He looked the most relaxed.

1195
01:03:05,487 --> 01:03:09,877
It means it's not so easy to be on this stage.

1196
01:03:09,877 --> 01:03:13,417
Hello, I've been acting for 12 years,

1197
01:03:13,417 --> 01:03:16,607
but I canceled my contract with the agency

1198
01:03:16,607 --> 01:03:20,587
to achieve my dream of becoming a director.

1199
01:03:20,587 --> 01:03:24,847
I'm Lee Yoo Jin, a new director
working on an independent film.

1200
01:03:26,157 --> 01:03:29,437
He is the person we know.

1201
01:03:29,437 --> 01:03:33,497
Yes. And he said he canceled the contract...

1202
01:03:33,497 --> 01:03:35,867
He wanted to tell us that.

1203
01:03:35,867 --> 01:03:38,127
It shows his resolve to be here.

1204
01:03:38,127 --> 01:03:40,957
Yoo Jin and I were under the same agency, too.

1205
01:03:40,957 --> 01:03:43,327
- I see.
- But he canceled the contract.

1206
01:03:43,327 --> 01:03:46,747
He left them to join another one,
but he left them, too.

1207
01:03:46,747 --> 01:03:49,077
- It wasn't personal against them.
- To become a director.

1208
01:03:49,077 --> 01:03:50,527
I know.

1209
01:03:50,527 --> 01:03:54,007
I have no title.

1210
01:03:54,007 --> 01:03:58,857
I'm not an actor. I haven't
debuted as a director, either.

1211
01:03:58,857 --> 01:04:04,637
But I wanted to become a director
even before I became an actor.

1212
01:04:04,637 --> 01:04:07,007
I'm working on a film right now.

1213
01:04:07,007 --> 01:04:09,657
I'm doing it in every possible way.

1214
01:04:09,657 --> 01:04:12,107
I know there's no perfect time.

1215
01:04:12,107 --> 01:04:13,867
[All he knows is to move forward]

1216
01:04:14,777 --> 01:04:19,837
You were in Lee Byeong Heon's "Be Melodramatic."

1217
01:04:19,837 --> 01:04:24,547
- Yes, that's correct.
- So, your nickname is "Be a Survivalist."

1218
01:04:24,547 --> 01:04:27,377
What does it mean? "Be a Survivalist"?

1219
01:04:27,377 --> 01:04:29,717
It costs a lot of money to make a film.

1220
01:04:29,717 --> 01:04:31,637
Of course.

1221
01:04:31,637 --> 01:04:33,967
I completely depleted my resources.

1222
01:04:33,967 --> 01:04:36,517
- What do you mean?
- On what?

1223
01:04:36,517 --> 01:04:38,447
I actually did.

1224
01:04:38,447 --> 01:04:40,657
- Do you mean...
- For the film?

1225
01:04:40,657 --> 01:04:43,907
- Yes, for the film.
- Not on entertainment and stuff.

1226
01:04:43,907 --> 01:04:46,637
You have to be more specific.

1227
01:04:46,637 --> 01:04:51,567
I know it's too forward to say this,

1228
01:04:51,567 --> 01:04:54,837
but I'm doing anything for money.

1229
01:04:54,837 --> 01:04:56,617
What have you been doing?

1230
01:04:56,617 --> 01:05:00,997
For example, I recently milked goats.

1231
01:05:00,997 --> 01:05:03,247
- What did you say?
- I milked goats...

1232
01:05:03,247 --> 01:05:05,527
Not just out of the blue, right?

1233
01:05:05,527 --> 01:05:08,137
To make money.

1234
01:05:08,137 --> 01:05:10,787
That'd be rude to the goats.

1235
01:05:10,787 --> 01:05:13,357
What kind of film is he making?

1236
01:05:13,357 --> 01:05:15,897
[Milking the goats to afford tomorrow's shoot]

1237
01:05:15,897 --> 01:05:17,717
Sorry.

1238
01:05:17,717 --> 01:05:20,197
I'm sorry for milking you so early.

1239
01:05:20,197 --> 01:05:22,367
I'm impressed with your determination.

1240
01:05:22,367 --> 01:05:25,637
I heard you might sell your parents' furniture.

1241
01:05:25,637 --> 01:05:29,017
- Why not his own?
- Wouldn't that be bad as a son?

1242
01:05:29,017 --> 01:05:33,737
I tend to do whatever it takes to reach my goals.

1243
01:05:33,737 --> 01:05:35,257
Anything for my goals.

1244
01:05:35,257 --> 01:05:37,997
I have no time, but no money, either.

1245
01:05:37,997 --> 01:05:43,057
To make money quickly,
I need to sell valuable things.

1246
01:05:43,057 --> 01:05:46,227
That's why I secretly...

1247
01:05:46,227 --> 01:05:48,097
I have to ask you this now.

1248
01:05:48,097 --> 01:05:52,487
Your father is Lee Hyo Jung, whom we all know.

1249
01:05:52,487 --> 01:05:56,487
- Mr. Lee Hyo Jung.
- Your uncle is Lee Ki Young.

1250
01:05:56,487 --> 01:05:59,917
[Actor Lee Hyo Jung's restaurant in Paju]

1251
01:05:59,917 --> 01:06:02,347
- Where's Dad?
- He's in the kitchen.

1252
01:06:02,347 --> 01:06:07,107
I told you I'll be on
a directing competition show.

1253
01:06:07,107 --> 01:06:12,817
I'm here to offer you a part.

1254
01:06:12,817 --> 01:06:15,107
I want my niece and nephew to be in it, too.

1255
01:06:15,107 --> 01:06:16,877
[For free?]

1256
01:06:16,877 --> 01:06:19,487
I brought many types of bribes.

1257
01:06:19,487 --> 01:06:21,617
This is a shampoo.

1258
01:06:21,617 --> 01:06:23,177
- Shampoo?
- What's that?

1259
01:06:23,177 --> 01:06:25,347
It's for graying hair.

1260
01:06:25,347 --> 01:06:27,077
This is what you need.

1261
01:06:27,077 --> 01:06:30,587
I work part-time in Imsil, you know.

1262
01:06:30,587 --> 01:06:32,727
Ta-da.

1263
01:06:32,727 --> 01:06:35,107
- Ta-da.
- What is it?

1264
01:06:35,107 --> 01:06:36,847
What is it? This is...

1265
01:06:36,847 --> 01:06:39,597
They had nice educational toys.

1266
01:06:39,597 --> 01:06:41,727
You hear the song, right?

1267
01:06:41,727 --> 01:06:45,587
<i>♫ In this land of beautiful rivers and mountains ♫</i>

1268
01:06:45,587 --> 01:06:49,197
<i>♫ King Dangun started our country ♫</i>

1269
01:06:49,197 --> 01:06:51,567
[I want to look at it, too]

1270
01:06:52,927 --> 01:06:56,517
[Determined to learn the entire history of Korea]

1271
01:06:56,517 --> 01:06:59,987
This will help you think about your goal.

1272
01:06:59,987 --> 01:07:01,897
I think it's a good opportunity.

1273
01:07:01,897 --> 01:07:05,667
I think it's a great idea to be on the show.

1274
01:07:05,667 --> 01:07:09,577
Do you agree to be in it, then?

1275
01:07:09,577 --> 01:07:12,597
Regarding that...

1276
01:07:12,597 --> 01:07:17,547
we probably should negotiate a bit.

1277
01:07:17,547 --> 01:07:21,127
- Give me some meat since I'm here.
- Meat?

1278
01:07:21,127 --> 01:07:24,687
This is based on a true story.

1279
01:07:24,687 --> 01:07:26,307
- True story?
- Yes.

1280
01:07:26,307 --> 01:07:28,867
Director and a former actor, Yoo Jin,

